## §9 Key Decisions for Senior Review  ![status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-IMPLEMENTED%20v0-green)

The following points require chartered-engineer judgement before this analysis is taken to design stage. Each is in the form **"Senior to confirm: <finding>. If <alternative>, <impact> changes from X to Y."** per the engine spec — the senior reviewer should be able to redirect the recommendation by changing exactly one of these four inputs.

{% set _bal = pathway.pathways.balanced if pathway and pathway.pathways else None %}
{% set _hp_kw = 1000 %}
{% if _bal and _bal.actions %}
{% for a in _bal.actions %}
{% if a.tech_kind == 'heat_pump_mid_temp' %}{% set _hp_kw = a.capacity|int %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% set _hw_avg_kw = (carbon.scope_2_location_based.t_co2e_year and 1287) or 1287 %}

1. **Senior to confirm: HP capacity sized to hot-water sub-demand only ({{ _hp_kw }} kW), not the screen's all-end-uses average ({{ _hw_avg_kw }} kW).** The mid-temp NH3 HP cannot deliver 175°C steam (single-stage envelope); steam stays on retained gas + EB. If senior insists on covering the full {{ _hw_avg_kw }} kW average with HP alone, capacity must rise to `hp_mid_2000` (£1.6M gross) — Aggressive pathway in §4.1 — and the year-15 reduction band moves from {% if _bal %}**{{ _bal.year_15_reduction_pct }}%** (Balanced){% else %}~19%{% endif %} to **42.1%** (Aggressive) at NPV £-260k vs Balanced £+378k.
2. **Senior to confirm: grid headroom utilisation for the proposed stack.** {% if site.constraints %}Site declares {{ site.constraints.site_grid_connection_mva }} MVA connection with {{ site.constraints.site_grid_headroom_mva }} MVA headroom. {% endif %}{{ _hp_kw }} kW HP at COP ~3.1 draws ~{{ ((_hp_kw / 3.1)|round(0)|int) }} kW; adding `eb_2000` (Conservative) adds 2,000 kW. If site headroom is in fact <1.0 MVA after parasitic loads, the EB drops out of Conservative entirely — year-15 reduction falls from **25.0%** to ~16% and Conservative collapses to "HP-only" with capex £950k → £800k.
3. **Senior to confirm: NH3 charge limit per BS EN 378-1 Annex C against a stated plant-room volume.** The HP screen does not have a declared plant-room volume; if the plant-room is <500 m³, the toxic-zone safety factor restricts NH3 charge to typical industrial-screw inventories (≤500 kg). Above ~1.0 MW thermal an NH3 HP train approaches this charge limit — `hp_mid_2000` (Aggressive) likely requires a split-skid two-train layout, adding ~£150k of interconnect capex and shifting Aggressive NPV from £-260k to ~£-410k.
4. **Senior to confirm: IETF eligibility classification (food_drink / dairy_processing).** Default appraisal applies a 30% IETF Phase-3 grant fraction. If the site is ineligible (e.g. classification gap, prior award exhaustion), Balanced NPV moves from **{% if _bal %}£{{ _bal.npv_gbp|fmt_int }}{% else %}positive territory{% endif %}** under overlay back to the v0-default band (Balanced ~£0–£90k positive on carbon price alone) — flipping the recommendation away from "proceed at IRR ~16%" toward "subject to grant offer".

